The paper discusses online optimization algorithms, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. The use of the alternating directions method (ADM) is also a common technique in optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses regret analysis, which is a common topic in online learning, making cs.OH (Online Learning) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also involves numerical optimization, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves optimization of constraints, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) possible sub-categories.
